{"word":"ἀνακαίω","slug":"ἀνακαίω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνακαίω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to light up</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to light oneself</i> a fire, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to fire up</i>, with anger, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}